# Styling With Tailwind

- Use Tailwind as the default styling approach.
- Prefer reusable patterns and utility composition over scattered one-off styling.
- Keep spacing, typography, and color usage consistent across the app.
- Optimize layouts for clarity, scanability, and information hierarchy.
- Use visual emphasis to support severity, confidence, and actionability without overstating risk.
- Avoid long unreadable class strings when extraction would improve maintenance.
- Keep inline styles rare and limited to cases Tailwind cannot express cleanly.
